Package com.horse.pokemon.ObjectData.Players Description

Contains all NPC and User information that is used to add functionality to the game. Two FunctionalInterfaces are made to aid with the User when detecting state changes from land to water transportation. AbstractPlayer is the superclass for all NPCs and Users, where they also extend Actor to contain an effective render using Actor.draw(com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.Batch, float), which is stored in a Stage and all Actors are drawn at nearly the same time and any actions created from Actor.addAction(com.badlogic.gdx.scenes.scene2d.Action) to make instant functions to the AbstractPlayer and its subclasses.
Since:
1.0
See Also:
